1
00:01:37,264 --> 00:01:39,156
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are you paying attention?</font>

2
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:43,661
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good.</font>

3
00:01:45,104 --> 00:01:48,623
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you're not listening carefully
you will miss things.</font>

4
00:01:50,027 --> 00:01:51,543
<font color="#FFFFFF">Important things.</font>

5
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:54,765
<font color="#FFFFFF">I will not pause,
I will not repeat myself</font>

6
00:01:54,865 --> 00:01:57,674
<font color="#FFFFFF">and you will not interrupt me.</font>

7
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:02,772
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you think that
because you're sitting where you are</font>

8
00:02:02,873 --> 00:02:04,274
<font color="#FFFFFF">and I am sitting where I am</font>

9
00:02:04,373 --> 00:02:08,644
<font color="#FFFFFF">that you are in control
of what is about to happen,</font>

10
00:02:09,754 --> 00:02:11,281
<font color="#FFFFFF">you're mistaken.</font>

11
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:13,574
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am in control,</font>

12
00:02:13,675 --> 00:02:16,776
<font color="#FFFFFF">because I know things
that you do not know.</font>

13
00:02:20,848 --> 00:02:22,960
<font color="#FFFFFF">Manchester Police Department.
Please hold.</font>

14
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:24,659
<font color="#FFFFFF">Looks like a break-in.</font>

15
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:26,796
<font color="#FFFFFF">Residence of Turing, Alan.</font>

16
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:29,039
<font color="#FFFFFF">Window's broken.
Home's been ransacked.</font>

17
00:02:29,525 --> 00:02:31,167
<font color="#FFFFFF">Send a detective down, will you?</font>

18
00:02:32,235 --> 00:02:33,929
<font color="#FFFFFF">What I will need from you now</font>

19
00:02:34,028 --> 00:02:36,014
<font color="#FFFFFF">is a commitment.</font>

20
00:02:36,114 --> 00:02:40,968
<font color="#FFFFFF">You will listen closely and you will not
judge me until I am finished.</font>

21
00:02:41,745 --> 00:02:44,930
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you cannot commit to this,
then please leave the room.</font>

22
00:02:46,082 --> 00:02:47,082
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come in.</font>

23
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:50,311
<font color="#FFFFFF">But if you choose to stay,
remember, you chose to be here.</font>

24
00:02:51,045 --> 00:02:54,439
<font color="#FFFFFF">What happens from this moment
forward is not my responsibility.</font>

25
00:02:55,341 --> 00:02:56,442
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's yours.</font>

26
00:03:00,222 --> 00:03:01,822
<font color="#FFFFFF">Pay attention.</font>

27
00:03:14,986 --> 00:03:16,138
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's all this, then?</font>

28
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:19,048
<font color="#FFFFFF">Turing, Alan. Professor at King's.</font>

29
00:03:19,949 --> 00:03:22,686
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Seems to have been a burglary.
- Oh? What of?</font>

30
00:03:22,786 --> 00:03:24,719
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, that's just it.
Nothing missing, really.</font>

31
00:03:26,163 --> 00:03:27,931
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's he doing in Manchester?</font>

32
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:31,060
<font color="#FFFFFF">Something with machines.</font>

33
00:03:38,551 --> 00:03:40,579
<font color="#FFFFFF">The project at the NPL.</font>

34
00:03:40,679 --> 00:03:43,280
<font color="#FFFFFF">I checked but he won't
say what it's on.</font>

35
00:03:45,474 --> 00:03:46,658
<font color="#FFFFFF">Professor Turing?</font>

36
00:03:46,977 --> 00:03:49,161
<font color="#FFFFFF">Detective Nock,
Manchester Police.</font>

37
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:56,252
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sergeant Staehl here tells me
you had a burglary last night.</font>

38
00:03:57,403 --> 00:03:58,628
<font color="#FFFFFF">Professor Turing?</font>

39
00:03:59,489 --> 00:04:02,633
<font color="#FFFFFF">Take a step back
and don't breathe heavily.</font>

40
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:05,229
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Breathe?
- Undiluted cyanide.</font>

41
00:04:05,329 --> 00:04:08,764
<font color="#FFFFFF">It wouldn't take more
than a thimbleful to kill you.</font>

42
00:04:09,707 --> 00:04:10,849
<font color="#FFFFFF">Ah.</font>

43
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:14,812
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Disappointing.
- Pardon?</font>

44
00:04:15,379 --> 00:04:17,824
<font color="#FFFFFF">I had hoped for a bit more.</font>

45
00:04:17,925 --> 00:04:21,125
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sergeant Staehl, is it just me or do you
get the sense that we're being insulted?</font>

46
00:04:21,595 --> 00:04:23,579
<font color="#FFFFFF">Last night you had a break-in.</font>

47
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:26,165
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your neighbour Mr. Springborn
called to report the noise.</font>

48
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:27,875
<font color="#FFFFFF">He said there was
quite a ruckus.</font>

49
00:04:27,975 --> 00:04:30,545
<font color="#FFFFFF">Only you say nothing was taken.
It's odd.</font>

50
00:04:30,646 --> 00:04:33,298
<font color="#FFFFFF">So how about you tell us what happened
and we'll find the chap who did this.</font>

51
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:35,509
<font color="#FFFFFF">Gentlemen,</font>

52
00:04:35,608 --> 00:04:38,553
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't believe that you could find
the chap that did this</font>

53
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:41,557
<font color="#FFFFFF">if he walked up to you
and spat in your face.</font>

54
00:04:41,656 --> 00:04:45,978
<font color="#FFFFFF">What I could use right now is not
a bobby but a really good cleaning lady.</font>

55
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:48,730
<font color="#FFFFFF">So unless one of you has an apron
in your car,</font>

56
00:04:48,829 --> 00:04:52,141
<font color="#FFFFFF">I suggest you file your reports
and leave me alone.</font>

57
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:56,062
<font color="#FFFFFF">As you say, Professor Turing.</font>

58
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:02,567
<font color="#FFFFFF">Best of luck with your cyanide.</font>

59
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:05,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'll give you a quid if you
can name me a more insufferable sod.</font>

60
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:07,915
<font color="#FFFFFF">Seemed a bit forced,
though, didn't it?</font>

61
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,543
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't know what you mean.</font>

62
00:05:09,643 --> 00:05:11,086
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, if you didn't
want a pair of bobbies</font>

63
00:05:11,185 --> 00:05:12,504
<font color="#FFFFFF">digging around in your
personal affairs,</font>

64
00:05:12,603 --> 00:05:15,538
<font color="#FFFFFF">that'd have been a stellar way
to make sure they don't.</font>

65
00:05:16,774 --> 00:05:18,259
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell me you don't think
this is suspicious.</font>

66
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,680
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't think this is suspicious.</font>

67
00:05:19,778 --> 00:05:21,596
<font color="#FFFFFF">A mysterious professor
who won't admit</font>

68
00:05:21,697 --> 00:05:23,588
<font color="#FFFFFF">he's had something stolen
from his house?</font>

69
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:28,218
<font color="#FFFFFF">I think Alan Turing's
hiding something.</font>

70
00:05:38,504 --> 00:05:41,699
<font color="#FFFFFF">War declared!
800,000 children evacuated!</font>

71
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,659
<font color="#FFFFFF">German bombs on their way!</font>

72
00:05:43,759 --> 00:05:44,911
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get your papers here.</font>

73
00:05:45,012 --> 00:05:46,079
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fresh off the press.</font>

74
00:05:46,178 --> 00:05:47,413
<font color="#FFFFFF">War declared!</font>

75
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:49,790
<font color="#FFFFFF">800,000 children evacuated!</font>

76
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:51,574
<font color="#FFFFFF">German bombs expected soon!</font>

77
00:05:52,144 --> 00:05:53,170
<font color="#FFFFFF">Get your papers here.</font>

78
00:05:53,269 --> 00:05:54,338
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fresh off the press.</font>

79
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:21,531
<font color="#FFFFFF">This morning,
the British Ambassador in Berlin</font>

80
00:06:21,630 --> 00:06:25,369
<font color="#FFFFFF">handed the German government
a final note,</font>

81
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:28,288
<font color="#FFFFFF">stating that unless
we heard from them</font>

82
00:06:28,387 --> 00:06:30,197
<font color="#FFFFFF">by 11 o'clock,</font>

83
00:06:30,432 --> 00:06:33,367
<font color="#FFFFFF">a state of war would
exist between us.</font>

84
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:36,379
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have to tell you now</font>

85
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,713
<font color="#FFFFFF">that no such undertaking</font>

86
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:39,247
<font color="#FFFFFF">has been received.</font>

87
00:06:40,317 --> 00:06:41,802
<font color="#FFFFFF">And that consequently,</font>

88
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:45,420
<font color="#FFFFFF">this country is at
war with Germany.</font>

89
00:07:12,516 --> 00:07:13,916
<font color="#FFFFFF">For the second time</font>

90
00:07:14,016 --> 00:07:16,076
<font color="#FFFFFF">in the lives of most of us,</font>

91
00:07:16,728 --> 00:07:19,663
<font color="#FFFFFF">we are at war.</font>

92
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:23,093
<font color="#FFFFFF">We have tried to find</font>

93
00:07:23,192 --> 00:07:25,961
<font color="#FFFFFF">a peaceful way out...</font>

94
00:07:28,949 --> 00:07:30,298
<font color="#FFFFFF">Papers, please.</font>

95
00:08:07,319 --> 00:08:10,923
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What are you doing here?
- Uh, the lady told me to wait.</font>

96
00:08:11,115 --> 00:08:12,548
<font color="#FFFFFF">In my office?</font>

97
00:08:13,785 --> 00:08:16,185
<font color="#FFFFFF">Did she tell you to help yourself to tea
while you were here?</font>

98
00:08:16,745 --> 00:08:18,346
<font color="#FFFFFF">Uh... No, she didn't.</font>

99
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:21,850
<font color="#FFFFFF">She obviously didn't tell you
what a joke was then, either, I gather?</font>

100
00:08:22,334 --> 00:08:23,685
<font color="#FFFFFF">Was she supposed to?</font>

101
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:28,064
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Who are you?
- Alan Turing.</font>

102
00:08:30,009 --> 00:08:33,496
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Ah, Turing. The mathematician.
- Correct.</font>

103
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,248
<font color="#FFFFFF">However could I have guessed?</font>

104
00:08:35,347 --> 00:08:37,408
<font color="#FFFFFF">You didn't.
You just read it on that piece of paper.</font>

105
00:08:39,476 --> 00:08:41,087
<font color="#FFFFFF">King's College, Cambridge.</font>

106
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:44,341
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now it says here you were a bit
of a prodigy in the Maths Department.</font>

107
00:08:44,441 --> 00:08:47,418
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm not sure I can
evaluate that, Mr...</font>

108
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:49,553
<font color="#FFFFFF">- How old are you, Mr. Turing?
- Uh, 27.</font>

109
00:08:49,653 --> 00:08:52,047
<font color="#FFFFFF">And how old were you when you
became a fellow at Cambridge?</font>

110
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:53,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">Twenty-four.</font>

111
00:08:53,283 --> 00:08:55,351
<font color="#FFFFFF">And how old were you
when you published this paper</font>

112
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:57,302
<font color="#FFFFFF">that has a title
that I can barely understand?</font>

113
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:59,188
<font color="#FFFFFF">Uh, 23.</font>

114
00:08:59,288 --> 00:09:02,224
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you don't think that qualifies you
as a certified prodigy?</font>

115
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:05,403
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, Newton discovered Binomial Theorem
aged 22.</font>

116
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:09,198
<font color="#FFFFFF">Einstein wrote four papers that changed
the world by the age of 26.</font>

117
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:12,735
<font color="#FFFFFF">As far as I can tell, I've...
I've barely made par.</font>

118
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:15,913
<font color="#FFFFFF">- My God, you're serious.
- Would you prefer I made a joke?</font>

119
00:09:16,014 --> 00:09:18,291
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, I don't think you know
what those are.</font>

120
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:19,918
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hardly seems fair
that that's a requirement</font>

121
00:09:20,018 --> 00:09:21,461
<font color="#FFFFFF">for employment here, Mr...</font>

122
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:23,296
<font color="#FFFFFF">Commander Denniston, Royal Navy.</font>

123
00:09:23,395 --> 00:09:24,923
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right, Mr. Turing, I'll bite.</font>

124
00:09:25,023 --> 00:09:27,416
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why do you wish to work
for His Majesty's Government?</font>

125
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:29,293
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, I don't, really.</font>

126
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,296
<font color="#FFFFFF">Are you a bleeding pacifist?</font>

127
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:35,466
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm agnostic about violence.</font>

128
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:38,227
<font color="#FFFFFF">But you do realise that 600 miles
away from London</font>

129
00:09:38,327 --> 00:09:40,312
<font color="#FFFFFF">there's this nasty little chap
called Hitler</font>

130
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:42,399
<font color="#FFFFFF">who wants to engulf
Europe in tyranny?</font>

131
00:09:42,499 --> 00:09:45,067
<font color="#FFFFFF">Politics isn't really my area
of expertise.</font>

132
00:09:45,168 --> 00:09:46,570
<font color="#FFFFFF">Really?</font>

133
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:48,488
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I believe
you've just set the record</font>

134
00:09:48,587 --> 00:09:51,240
<font color="#FFFFFF">for the shortest job interview
in British military history.</font>

135
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:52,826
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, uh...</font>

136
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:54,566
<font color="#FFFFFF">Mother says I can be
off-putting sometimes</font>

137
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:57,114
<font color="#FFFFFF">on account of being one of the best
mathematicians in the world.</font>

138
00:09:57,429 --> 00:09:59,615
<font color="#FFFFFF">- In the world?
- Oh, yes.</font>

139
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:03,669
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you know how many people
I've rejected for this programme?</font>

140
00:10:03,769 --> 00:10:05,004
<font color="#FFFFFF">- No.
- That's right.</font>

141
00:10:05,105 --> 00:10:06,798
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because we're a top
secret programme.</font>

142
00:10:06,898 --> 00:10:09,091
<font color="#FFFFFF">But I'll tell you,
just because we're friends,</font>

143
00:10:09,192 --> 00:10:13,596
<font color="#FFFFFF">that only last week I rejected
one of our great nation's top linguists.</font>

144
00:10:13,697 --> 00:10:15,974
<font color="#FFFFFF">Knows German better
than Bertolt Brecht.</font>

145
00:10:16,073 --> 00:10:18,008
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I don't speak German.
- What?</font>

146
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:22,022
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't speak German.</font>

147
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:25,024
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, how the hell are you supposed
to decrypt German communications</font>

148
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:27,652
<font color="#FFFFFF">if you don't...
I don't know, speak German?</font>

149
00:10:27,751 --> 00:10:29,871
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I'm really quite excellent
at crossword puzzles.</font>

150
00:10:30,254 --> 00:10:31,780
<font color="#FFFFFF">Margaret!</font>

151
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:35,493
<font color="#FFFFFF">German codes are a puzzle.
A game just like any other game.</font>

152
00:10:35,592 --> 00:10:37,120
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Margaret, where are you?
- I'm really very good at games,</font>

153
00:10:37,220 --> 00:10:38,220
<font color="#FFFFFF">uh, puzzles.</font>

154
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:40,789
<font color="#FFFFFF">And this is the most difficult puzzle
in the world.</font>

155
00:10:40,889 --> 00:10:42,375
<font color="#FFFFFF">Margaret!</font>

156
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:43,991
<font color="#FFFFFF">For the love of God.</font>

157
00:10:44,311 --> 00:10:45,661
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is a joke, obviously.</font>

158
00:10:46,730 --> 00:10:50,331
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm afraid I don't know what those are,
Commander Denniston.</font>

159
00:10:50,899 --> 00:10:52,885
<font color="#FFFFFF">Have a pleasant trip back
to Cambridge, Professor.</font>

160
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:54,086
<font color="#FFFFFF">Enigma.</font>

161
00:10:54,403 --> 00:10:55,754
<font color="#FFFFFF">You called for me?</font>

162
00:11:04,246 --> 00:11:08,525
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's what you're doing here.
The top secret programme at Bletchley.</font>

163
00:11:08,625 --> 00:11:11,894
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're trying to break
the German Enigma machine.</font>

164
00:11:12,589 --> 00:11:14,355
<font color="#FFFFFF">What makes you think that?</font>

165
00:11:15,091 --> 00:11:17,076
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's the greatest encryption device
in history</font>

166
00:11:17,177 --> 00:11:20,413
<font color="#FFFFFF">and the Germans use it
for all major communications.</font>

167
00:11:20,513 --> 00:11:23,740
<font color="#FFFFFF">If the Allies broke Enigma, well,</font>

168
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:28,412
<font color="#FFFFFF">this would turn into
a very short war indeed.</font>

169
00:11:28,645 --> 00:11:31,173
<font color="#FFFFFF">Of course that's what
you're working on.</font>

170
00:11:31,274 --> 00:11:32,754
<font color="#FFFFFF">You also haven't got
anywhere with it.</font>

171
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:35,595
<font color="#FFFFFF">If you had, you wouldn't be hiring
cryptographers out of university.</font>

172
00:11:35,695 --> 00:11:38,254
<font color="#FFFFFF">You need me a lot
more than I need you.</font>

173
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:41,466
<font color="#FFFFFF">I... I like solving
problems, Commander.</font>

174
00:11:42,826 --> 00:11:46,221
<font color="#FFFFFF">And Enigma is the most difficult
problem in the world.</font>

175
00:11:46,498 --> 00:11:48,724
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, Enigma isn't difficult.
It's impossible.</font>

176
00:11:48,957 --> 00:11:51,225
<font color="#FFFFFF">The Americans, the
Russians, the French,</font>

177
00:11:51,543 --> 00:11:54,605
<font color="#FFFFFF">the Germans.
Everyone thinks Enigma is unbreakable.</font>

178
00:11:55,130 --> 00:11:58,900
<font color="#FFFFFF">Good. Let me try,
then we'll know for sure, won't we?</font>

179
