<font color="#FFFFFF">A gunnery ensign.</font>

1159
01:22:23,646 --> 01:22:25,122
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm...</font>

1160
01:22:27,192 --> 01:22:28,751
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm so sorry.</font>

1161
01:22:31,363 --> 01:22:33,756
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who the hell do you
think you are?</font>

1162
01:22:34,490 --> 01:22:35,966
<font color="#FFFFFF">This... This is my brother.</font>

1163
01:22:38,369 --> 01:22:39,810
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look, he's my big
brother, all right?</font>

1164
01:22:39,872 --> 01:22:41,832
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you have a few minutes
to call off his murder.</font>

1165
01:22:42,457 --> 01:22:44,434
<font color="#FFFFFF">We can't.</font>

1166
01:22:46,045 --> 01:22:47,603
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's right.</font>

1167
01:22:48,671 --> 01:22:50,230
<font color="#FFFFFF">Alan...</font>

1168
01:22:51,050 --> 01:22:52,608
<font color="#FFFFFF">Joan...</font>

1169
01:22:54,386 --> 01:22:56,487
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hugh... John.</font>

1170
01:22:58,556 --> 01:23:00,542
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, please, I...</font>

1171
01:23:00,643 --> 01:23:02,461
<font color="#FFFFFF">The Germans, they
won't get suspicious</font>

1172
01:23:02,560 --> 01:23:04,162
<font color="#FFFFFF">just because we stop one attack.</font>

1173
01:23:04,646 --> 01:23:06,163
<font color="#FFFFFF">No one will know.</font>

1174
01:23:07,024 --> 01:23:09,625
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm asking you as your friend.</font>

1175
01:23:11,153 --> 01:23:12,670
<font color="#FFFFFF">Please.</font>

1176
01:23:16,240 --> 01:23:17,800
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm so sorry.</font>

1177
01:23:19,078 --> 01:23:22,430
<font color="#FFFFFF">You're not God, Alan, you don't
get to decide who lives and who dies.</font>

1178
01:23:23,332 --> 01:23:24,806
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, we do.</font>

1179
01:23:28,045 --> 01:23:29,279
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why?</font>

1180
01:23:29,380 --> 01:23:31,773
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because no one else can.</font>

1181
01:24:20,055 --> 01:24:21,572
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why are you telling me this?</font>

1182
01:24:22,807 --> 01:24:28,078
<font color="#FFFFFF">We need your help to keep this a secret
from Admiralty, Army, RAF.</font>

1183
01:24:29,814 --> 01:24:34,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">No one can know we broke Enigma.
Not even Denniston.</font>

1184
01:24:35,654 --> 01:24:37,712
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who's in the process
of having you fired.</font>

1185
01:24:38,073 --> 01:24:39,590
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can take care of that.</font>

1186
01:24:40,117 --> 01:24:42,226
<font color="#FFFFFF">While we develop a system
to help you determine</font>

1187
01:24:42,327 --> 01:24:45,314
<font color="#FFFFFF">how much intelligence to act on.</font>

1188
01:24:45,413 --> 01:24:47,890
<font color="#FFFFFF">Which, er, attacks to stop,
which to let through.</font>

1189
01:24:48,500 --> 01:24:50,319
<font color="#FFFFFF">Statistical analysis.</font>

1190
01:24:50,418 --> 01:24:54,188
<font color="#FFFFFF">The minimal number of actions
it would take for us to win the war</font>

1191
01:24:55,340 --> 01:24:59,860
<font color="#FFFFFF">but the maximum number we can take
before the Germans get suspicious.</font>

1192
01:25:00,511 --> 01:25:03,780
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you're going to
trust all this to statistics?</font>

1193
01:25:05,184 --> 01:25:06,668
<font color="#FFFFFF">- To maths?
- Correct.</font>

1194
01:25:06,769 --> 01:25:10,338
<font color="#FFFFFF">And then MI6 can come up with
the lies that we tell everybody else.</font>

1195
01:25:10,439 --> 01:25:12,591
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'll need a believable
alternative source</font>

1196
01:25:12,690 --> 01:25:15,260
<font color="#FFFFFF">for all the pieces
of information you use.</font>

1197
01:25:15,359 --> 01:25:17,429
<font color="#FFFFFF">A false story so
that we can explain</font>

1198
01:25:17,529 --> 01:25:20,431
<font color="#FFFFFF">how we got our information
that has nothing to do with Enigma.</font>

1199
01:25:20,532 --> 01:25:23,601
<font color="#FFFFFF">And then you can leak those
stories to the, er, the Germans.</font>

1200
01:25:23,702 --> 01:25:25,386
<font color="#FFFFFF">And then to our own military.</font>

1201
01:25:31,542 --> 01:25:35,729
<font color="#FFFFFF">Maintain a conspiracy of lies
at the highest levels of government?</font>

1202
01:25:44,139 --> 01:25:45,907
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sounds right up my alley.</font>

1203
01:25:49,728 --> 01:25:53,047
<font color="#FFFFFF">Alan, I so rarely
have cause to say this,</font>

1204
01:25:53,148 --> 01:25:56,667
<font color="#FFFFFF">but you are exactly the man
I always hoped you would be.</font>

1205
01:26:10,582 --> 01:26:13,444
<font color="#FFFFFF">They codenamed it Ultra.</font>

1206
01:26:13,543 --> 01:26:17,989
<font color="#FFFFFF">It became the largest store
of military intelligence</font>

1207
01:26:18,090 --> 01:26:19,814
<font color="#FFFFFF">in the history of the world.</font>

1208
01:26:26,765 --> 01:26:29,867
<font color="#FFFFFF">It was like having a tap
on Himmler's intercom.</font>

1209
01:26:30,601 --> 01:26:32,161
<font color="#FFFFFF">I-E-O...</font>

1210
01:26:33,396 --> 01:26:34,797
<font color="#FFFFFF">T-X-X...</font>

1211
01:26:34,898 --> 01:26:37,091
<font color="#FFFFFF">Secrecy became the primary concern</font>

1212
01:26:37,192 --> 01:26:40,168
<font color="#FFFFFF">and for some reason, they...
They trusted me.</font>

1213
01:26:41,947 --> 01:26:46,550
<font color="#FFFFFF">Peter, do you have the, er...
the 6:30 decrypt?</font>

1214
01:27:27,158 --> 01:27:28,685
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's a Beale cipher.</font>

1215
01:27:28,784 --> 01:27:30,229
<font color="#FFFFFF">Encrypted with a
phrase from a...</font>

1216
01:27:30,328 --> 01:27:33,148
<font color="#FFFFFF">"Ask, and it shall be given
to you; seek and ye will find."</font>

1217
01:27:33,247 --> 01:27:35,692
<font color="#FFFFFF">Matthew 7:7.
That was the key.</font>

1218
01:27:35,792 --> 01:27:38,101
<font color="#FFFFFF">Peter will come
around eventually.</font>

1219
01:27:46,677 --> 01:27:48,497
<font color="#FFFFFF">Jack?</font>

1220
01:27:48,596 --> 01:27:50,613
<font color="#FFFFFF">Could you give Alan
and me a moment, please?</font>

1221
01:28:02,444 --> 01:28:05,421
<font color="#FFFFFF">The Soviets and us,
we're on the same side.</font>

1222
01:28:06,323 --> 01:28:08,891
<font color="#FFFFFF">What I'm doing
will help Britain.</font>

1223
01:28:08,992 --> 01:28:11,594
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have to tell Denniston.</font>

1224
01:28:12,537 --> 01:28:13,887
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, you don't.</font>

1225
01:28:15,122 --> 01:28:17,307
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because if you tell
him my secret,</font>

1226
01:28:18,210 --> 01:28:19,643
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'll tell him yours.</font>

1227
01:28:22,046 --> 01:28:24,731
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you know what they
do to homosexuals?</font>

1228
01:28:25,884 --> 01:28:28,912
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'll never be able to work again.
Never be able to teach.</font>

1229
01:28:29,011 --> 01:28:30,488
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your precious machine?</font>

1230
01:28:31,555 --> 01:28:33,657
<font color="#FFFFFF">I doubt you'll ever
see him again.</font>

1231
01:28:49,740 --> 01:28:51,059
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hello. Can I...</font>

1232
01:28:51,158 --> 01:28:53,979
<font color="#FFFFFF">um, speak to Stewart Menzies,
please? It's urgent.</font>

1233
01:28:54,078 --> 01:28:56,096
<font color="#FFFFFF">One moment, please.</font>

1234
01:28:59,417 --> 01:29:01,018
<font color="#FFFFFF">Hello. Menzies.</font>

1235
01:29:04,338 --> 01:29:07,315
<font color="#FFFFFF">Some advice about keeping secrets.</font>

1236
01:29:09,761 --> 01:29:13,530
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's a lot easier if you
don't know them in the first place.</font>

1237
01:29:14,599 --> 01:29:18,837
<font color="#FFFFFF">Were they steaming my letters,
tapping my telephone?</font>

1238
01:29:18,936 --> 01:29:21,287
<font color="#FFFFFF">Trailing my nervous walks?</font>

1239
01:29:22,399 --> 01:29:23,791
<font color="#FFFFFF">You know, I...</font>

1240
01:29:24,775 --> 01:29:26,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">I never did find out.</font>

1241
01:29:27,445 --> 01:29:29,003
<font color="#FFFFFF">Joan?</font>

1242
01:29:33,243 --> 01:29:35,010
<font color="#FFFFFF">Joan? What's...</font>

1243
01:29:37,872 --> 01:29:40,181
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh. Where's Joan?</font>

1244
01:29:41,626 --> 01:29:43,351
<font color="#FFFFFF">Military prison.</font>

1245
01:29:45,796 --> 01:29:47,698
<font color="#FFFFFF">What have you done?</font>

1246
01:29:47,798 --> 01:29:49,326
<font color="#FFFFFF">Decoded Enigma intercepts.</font>

1247
01:29:49,426 --> 01:29:51,203
<font color="#FFFFFF">I found a pile of them
in the bedside table.</font>

1248
01:29:51,302 --> 01:29:54,497
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, no. I... I gave those to her
over a year ago</font>

1249
01:29:54,597 --> 01:29:56,375
<font color="#FFFFFF">when I was trying to figure out</font>

1250
01:29:56,475 --> 01:29:58,335
<font color="#FFFFFF">- a link between...
- I'm sure you did.</font>

1251
01:29:58,435 --> 01:30:00,378
<font color="#FFFFFF">Denniston's been looking
for a Soviet spy.</font>

1252
01:30:00,479 --> 01:30:02,037
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's been looking inside Hut 8.</font>

1253
01:30:03,981 --> 01:30:05,498
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know who the spy is.</font>

1254
01:30:07,109 --> 01:30:09,043
<font color="#FFFFFF">It... It's not Joan. It's...</font>

1255
01:30:10,654 --> 01:30:12,724
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's Cairncross.</font>

1256
01:30:12,823 --> 01:30:16,051
<font color="#FFFFFF">I... I found the Beale cipher,
the Bible.</font>

1257
01:30:17,328 --> 01:30:19,721
<font color="#FFFFFF">God, I wish you'd been the spy.</font>

1258
01:30:21,291 --> 01:30:23,184
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'd be so much better
at this than he is.</font>

1259
01:30:24,795 --> 01:30:26,570
<font color="#FFFFFF">You knew it was him?</font>

1260
01:30:26,671 --> 01:30:28,489
<font color="#FFFFFF">Of course I bloody knew.</font>

1261
01:30:28,590 --> 01:30:30,774
<font color="#FFFFFF">I knew before he
came to Bletchley.</font>

1262
01:30:31,592 --> 01:30:33,113
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why do you think I
had him placed here?</font>

1263
01:30:33,177 --> 01:30:35,904
<font color="#FFFFFF">But we have an Enigma machine.</font>

1264
01:30:36,139 --> 01:30:37,416
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, Polish Intelligence smuggled...</font>

1265
01:30:37,515 --> 01:30:38,917
<font color="#FFFFFF">So what's the problem?</font>

1266
01:30:39,016 --> 01:30:43,505
<font color="#FFFFFF">You placed a...
a Soviet agent at Bletchley Park?</font>

1267
01:30:43,604 --> 01:30:46,916
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's really quite useful to be able to
leak whatever we want to Stalin.</font>

1268
01:30:48,609 --> 01:30:50,845
<font color="#FFFFFF">Churchill's too damn paranoid.</font>

1269
01:30:50,945 --> 01:30:54,890
<font color="#FFFFFF">He won't share a shred
of intelligence with the Soviets.</font>

1270
01:30:54,990 --> 01:30:57,269
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not even information that
will help them against the Germans.</font>

1271
01:30:57,368 --> 01:31:00,304
<font color="#FFFFFF">There's... so much secrecy.</font>

1272
01:31:02,123 --> 01:31:05,109
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cairncross has no idea
we know, of course.</font>

1273
01:31:05,210 --> 01:31:07,810
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's really not the
brightest bulb.</font>

1274
01:31:09,171 --> 01:31:11,408
<font color="#FFFFFF">Which is why I need your help.</font>

1275
01:31:11,507 --> 01:31:13,118
<font color="#FFFFFF">I want to know what
to leak to John,</font>

1276
01:31:13,217 --> 01:31:15,912
<font color="#FFFFFF">what to feed to the Soviets
as well as the British.</font>

1277
01:31:16,011 --> 01:31:17,570
<font color="#FFFFFF">I...</font>

1278
01:31:18,055 --> 01:31:20,615
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm not a... I'm not a spy.
I'm...</font>

1279
01:31:21,309 --> 01:31:23,878
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm just a mathematician.</font>

1280
01:31:23,979 --> 01:31:26,162
<font color="#FFFFFF">I know a lot of spies, Alan.</font>

1281
01:31:27,314 --> 01:31:30,417
<font color="#FFFFFF">You've got more secrets
than the best of them.</font>

1282
01:31:34,655 --> 01:31:38,259
<font color="#FFFFFF">You... You have to promise me
that you will release Joan.</font>

1283
01:31:38,993 --> 01:31:40,395
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, Joan's at the market.</font>

1284
01:31:40,494 --> 01:31:42,845
<font color="#FFFFFF">She's going to be back
in an hour. I lied.</font>

1285
01:31:44,916 --> 01:31:46,777
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'd better hold on to these.</font>

1286
01:31:46,877 --> 01:31:50,813
<font color="#FFFFFF">If anybody finds out about them,
prison will be the least of her worries.</font>

1287
01:31:53,216 --> 01:31:54,692
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, Alan,</font>

1288
01:31:56,051 --> 01:31:58,779
<font color="#FFFFFF">we're going to have
such a wonderful war together.</font>

1289
01:32:18,115 --> 01:32:19,684
<font color="#FFFFFF">I need you to leave Bletchley.</font>

1290
01:32:19,783 --> 01:32:20,851
<font color="#FFFFFF">What?</font>

1291
01:32:20,952 --> 01:32:23,354
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's Menzies. I don't trust him.</font>

1292
01:32:23,454 --> 01:32:25,106
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's not safe here.</font>

1293
01:32:25,207 --> 01:32:26,846
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you think it's
any safer anywhere else?</font>

1294
01:32:26,875 --> 01:32:29,277
<font color="#FFFFFF">You need to get away.
You need to get very far away from me.</font>

1295
01:32:29,377 --> 01:32:30,894
<font color="#FFFFFF">Alan, what's happened?</font>

1296
01:32:35,300 --> 01:32:37,868
<font color="#FFFFFF">We can't be engaged any more.
You...</font>

1297
01:32:37,969 --> 01:32:41,572
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your parents need to take you back
and find you a husband elsewhere.</font>

1298
01:32:43,390 --> 01:32:45,576
<font color="#FFFFFF">What's wrong with you?</font>

1299
01:32:46,435 --> 01:32:49,371
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have something,
er, to tell you.</font>

1300
01:32:49,648 --> 01:32:50,913
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm...</font>

1301
01:32:53,984 --> 01:32:55,711
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm a homosexual.</font>

1302
01:32:58,739 --> 01:33:01,925
<font color="#FFFFFF">- All right.
- No, no. Men, Joan.</font>

1303
01:33:03,578 --> 01:33:05,429
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Not women.
- So what?</font>

1304
01:33:06,497 --> 01:33:08,024
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I... I just told you.</font>

1305
01:33:08,123 --> 01:33:09,600
<font color="#FFFFFF">So what?</font>

1306
01:33:12,671 --> 01:33:14,938
<font color="#FFFFFF">I had my suspicions,
I always did.</font>

1307
01:33:16,173 --> 01:33:20,036
<font color="#FFFFFF">But we're not like other people.
We love each other in our own way</font>

1308
01:33:20,136 --> 01:33:22,204
<font color="#FFFFFF">and we can have the life together
that we want.</font>

1309
01:33:22,305 --> 01:33:24,739
<font color="#FFFFFF">You... You won't be
the perfect husband.</font>

1310
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:28,837
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well, I can promise you, I harbour
no intention of being the perfect wife.</font>

1311
01:33:28,936 --> 01:33:33,425
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'll not be fixing your lamb all day
while you come home from the office.</font>

1312
01:33:33,524 --> 01:33:35,125
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'll work.</font>

1313
01:33:35,944 --> 01:33:37,461
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'll work.</font>

1314
01:33:39,029 --> 01:33:41,131
<font color="#FFFFFF">And we'll have each
other's company.</font>

1315
01:33:41,865 --> 01:33:44,259
<font color="#FFFFFF">We'll have each other's minds.</font>

1316
01:33:44,661 --> 01:33:47,429
<font color="#FFFFFF">That sounds like a better
marriage than most.</font>

1317
01:33:49,707 --> 01:33:51,432
<font color="#FFFFFF">Because I care for you.</font>

1318
01:33:52,877 --> 01:33:54,560
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you care for me.</font>

1319
01:33:56,547 --> 01:33:58,199
<font color="#FFFFFF">And we understand
one another more than...</font>

1320
01:33:58,300 --> 01:34:00,818
<font color="#FFFFFF">more than anyone else ever has.</font>

1321
01:34:02,554 --> 01:34:04,070
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't.</font>

1322
01:34:07,725 --> 01:34:09,451
<font color="#FFFFFF">- What?
- Care for you.</font>

1323
01:34:10,228 --> 01:34:11,630
<font color="#FFFFFF">I never did.</font>

1324
01:34:11,729 --> 01:34:14,757
<font color="#FFFFFF">I... I just needed
you to break Enigma.</font>

1325
01:34:14,858 --> 01:34:17,751
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've done that now, so...
So you can go.</font>

1326
01:34:23,490 --> 01:34:25,634
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm not going anywhere.</font>

1327
01:34:26,869 --> 01:34:28,646
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've spent entirely
too much of my life</font>

1328
01:34:28,747 --> 01:34:30,231
<font color="#FFFFFF">worried about what
you think of me</font>

1329
01:34:30,332 --> 01:34:32,234
<font color="#FFFFFF">or what my parents think of me</font>

1330
01:34:32,333 --> 01:34:34,402
<font color="#FFFFFF">or the boys in Hut 8
or the girls in Hut 3.</font>

1331
01:34:34,502 --> 01:34:36,185
<font color="#FFFFFF">And do you know what? I'm done.</font>

1332
01:34:37,671 --> 01:34:40,908
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is the most important
work I will ever do</font>

1333
01:34:41,009 --> 01:34:44,485
<font color="#FFFFFF">and no one is going to stop me,
least of all you.</font>

1334
01:34:47,265 --> 01:34:49,783
<font color="#FFFFFF">Do you know what?
They were right.</font>

1335
01:34:50,601 --> 01:34:52,869
<font color="#FFFFFF">Peter, Hugh, John.</font>

1336
01:34:56,399 --> 01:34:58,125
<font color="#FFFFFF">You really are a monster.</font>

1337
01:35:17,002 --> 01:35:21,814
<font color="#FFFFFF">The war dragged on
for two more solitary years</font>

1338
01:35:24,135 --> 01:35:27,945
<font color="#FFFFFF">and every day we performed
our blood-soaked calculus.</font>

1339
01:35:30,100 --> 01:35:33,420
<font color="#FFFFFF">Every day we decided
who lived and who died.</font>

1340
01:35:33,520 --> 01:35:38,457
<font color="#FFFFFF">Every day we helped the Allies
to victories and nobody knew.</font>

1341
01:35:42,569 --> 01:35:44,128
<font color="#FFFFFF">Stalingrad.</font>

1342
01:35:44,905 --> 01:35:47,925
<font color="#FFFFFF">The Ardenne.
The invasion of Normandy.</font>

1343
01:35:48,993 --> 01:35:51,145
<font color="#FFFFFF">All victories that would not
have been possible</font>

1344
01:35:51,246 --> 01:35:53,471
<font color="#FFFFFF">without the intelligence
that we supplied.</font>

1345
01:35:54,748 --> 01:35:57,652
<font color="#FFFFFF">And people talk about the war</font>

1346
01:35:57,752 --> 01:36:01,813
<font color="#FFFFFF">as this epic battle
between civilisations.</font>

1347
01:36:03,550 --> 01:36:07,069
<font color="#FFFFFF">Freedom versus tyranny.
Democracy versus Nazism.</font>

1348
01:36:08,637 --> 01:36:12,751
<font color="#FFFFFF">Armies of millions
bleeding into the ground.</font>

1349
01:36:12,850 --> 01:36:16,003
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fleets of ships
weighing down the oceans.</font>

1350
01:36:16,104 --> 01:36:20,122
<font color="#FFFFFF">Planes dropping bombs from the sky
until they obliterated the sun itself.</font>

